FortSetting.AnnualRefundTokenRequests_Description:
<text size="22">Cancel Purchase</>

You may cancel any unintentional purchase made with V-Bucks. Cancel Purchase is available until you equip or use your purchase during gameplay. Only items purchased within the last 24 hours are eligible for Cancel Purchase.

For more info see fn.gg/cancelpurchase

<text size="24">Returning Purchases</>

In cases where you unintentionally purchase an item with V-Bucks and purchase cancelation is no longer available, you can use one of your 3 annual Return Tickets instead. Youll receive one additional Return Ticket every 12 months, up to a maximum of 3. Each ticket is added 12 months following the most recent ticket you received.

FortSetting.ScopedSpeedMultiplier_Description: A multiplier that is applied to the look sensitivity when aiming down sights with scoped weapons.  Settings less than 1x will decrease sensitivity when aiming down scope.  Settings greater than 1x will increase sensitivity when aiming down scope.

FortSetting.GyroV2Acceleration_Description:
Acceleration lets you increase your aim sensitivity when turning the controller quickly.

Acceleration can give you a wider range of movement while still keeping your sensitivity low when you want to keep your aim steady. Acceleration is capped so that your fast movements are still consistent and predictable. Selecting CUSTOM will give you more control over the acceleration cap and where it's applied.

The LEGACY option is for those who want their gyro acceleration to feel the same as it did in older versions.

FortSetting.LockPrimaryInputMethodToMouse_Descriptio: Allows using Controller Input and Mouse Input together, and locks the input feedback to Mouse and Keyboard suggestions, rather than having the input methods fight.
FortSetting.EnablePreferredItemSlots_Description:
Allows you to assign a preferred inventory slot for a weapon or item type. On pick up, your preferred item will be placed into its preferred inventory slot.

Unassigned items will be placed in the first available quickbar slot and rearranged if a preferred item type is picked up. 

 Rarity swapping will occur when picking up a higher rarity like-for-like item. Eg. Uncommon Pump Shotgun will swap for an Epic Pump Shotgun. The lower rarity item will be relocated to the first available slot.

 Auto-Sort Consumables to Right will continue to work with Preferred Item Slots.

 Preferred item slots will only be active when you have at least one empty inventory slot.
FortSetting.KBMBindingPreset_Description: Allows you to reset the bindings to the keys to a new preset.
FortSetting.ControllerBindingPreset_Description:
Allows you to select which controller preset to use.

<strong>Old School</>: Original controls for Fortnite.

<strong>Quick Builder</>: A preset that focuses on quick building.

<strong>Combat Pro</>: A preset that focuses on combat.

<strong>Builder Pro (Default)</>: A preset that focuses on building. <strong>This is the recommended default for Fortnite.</>

<strong>Custom</>: Custom controls set by the mappings below.
FortSetting.LookHorizontalBoostSpeedAds_Description: An additional left/right rotation speed applied when the controller's right stick is fully deflected while aiming down sights.  Using boost allows for quicker turns while maintaining look precision.  Set to 0% to disable horizontal boost.
FortSetting.LookHorizontalBoostSpeed_Description: An additional left/right rotation speed applied when the controller's right stick is fully deflected.  Using boost allows for quicker turns while maintaining look precision.  Set to 0% to disable horizontal boost.
FortSetting.LookVerticalBoostSpeedAds_Description: An additional up/down rotation speed applied when the controller's right stick is fully deflected while aiming down sights.  Using boost allows for quicker turns while maintaining look precision.  Set to 0% to disable vertical boost.
FortSetting.LookVerticalBoostSpeed_Description: An additional up/down rotation speed applied when the controller's right stick is fully deflected.  Using boost allows for quicker turns while maintaining look precision.  Set to 0% to disable vertical boost.
FortSetting.AntiAliasingSuperResolution_Description:
Anti-Aliasing smooths jagged edges and can stabilize the image under motion. Super Resolution methods do the same while additionally improving performance by rendering fewer pixels each frame to generate the same resolution output image.

Off: Anti-Aliasing is turned off.

FXAA: Fast Approximate Anti-Aliasing requires less computing power, but being a spatial only anti-aliasing technique, it may result in flickering.

TAA: Temporal Anti-Aliasing combines previous frames with the current frame to provide a better quality than FXAA.

TSR Low/Medium/High/Epic: Temporal Super Resolution improves anti-aliasing quality, and overall rendering performance, by rendering fewer pixels each frame to produce comparable visual quality output image.

FortSetting.VoiceChatMethod_Description_Mobile:

<strong>Open Mic</>: Your microphone is always on and other players hear you at all times.

<strong>Toggle Voice</>: Other players will only hear you talking when you activate your microphone by tapping the Toggle Voice button.
FortSetting.VoiceChatMethod_Description_WithMute_Mob:
Determines whether your microphone is an <strong>open mic</>, or requires a <strong>toggle button</> to activate/deactivate, or is <strong>muted</>.

<strong>OPEN MIC:</> Your microphone is always on and your teammates can hear you at all times.

<strong>TOGGLE VOICE:</> Other players will only hear you talking when you activate your microphone by tapping the "Toggle Voice" button.

<strong>MIC MUTED:</> Your microphone is off and your teammates cannot hear you.
FortSetting.VoiceChatMethod_Description_WithMute:

<strong>OPEN MIC:</> Your microphone is always on and your teammates can hear you at all times.

<strong>PUSH TO TALK:</> Your microphone is only on and teammates will only hear you talking when you press and hold the 'push to talk' control. The push to talk button can be set in the Keyboard Controls tab.

<strong>MIC MUTED:</> Your microphone is off and your teammates cannot hear you.
FortSetting.VoiceChatMethod_Description:
Determines whether your microphone is an <strong>open mic</>, or requires a button <strong>push to talk</>.

<strong>Open Mic</>: Your microphone is always on and your teammates hear you at all times.

<strong>Push to Talk</>: Your microphone is only on and teammates will only hear you talking when you press and hold the 'push to talk' control. The push to talk button can be set in the Keyboard Controls tab.

FortSetting.MissingSM6: DirectX 12 requires SM6 shaders which are not currently installed. These shaders can be installed from the Fortnite options located in the launcher.
FortSetting.GamepadVibrationBlocksDevice_Description: Disables device vibration when a controller is attached.
FortSetting.GyroDisabledWhileDriving_Description: Disables gyro aiming while in the driver's seat of a vehicle.
FortSetting.Resolution_Description: Display Resolution determines the size of the window in Windowed mode. In Fullscreen mode, Display Resolution determines the graphics card output resolution, which can result in black bars depending on monitor and graphics card. Display Resolution is inactive in Windowed Fullscreen mode.
FortSetting.CosmeticStreaming_Description:
Download only the necessary cosmetics when you encounter them while playing.

NOTE: Slower internet connections may experience performance issues when the game is streaming cosmetics. Turning this feature off will require more disk space.

ON: Fortnite will only download cosmetics encountered in-game.

OFF: Fortnite will download all cosmetics.
FortSetting.CanSeeOtherPlayersNames_Desc:
During a match, the account names of players who are eliminated will appear on the screen.
This setting allows you to replace the names of other players who are not in your squad with "Player" in those messages.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Note</>: You will still be able to see the names of people in the same "squad" (up to three other players on your team who may or may not be friends).
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: You will see the names of players that are not squad members.
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: Replaces the names of players that are not in your squad with "Player"
FortSetting.CanDisplayMyUserName_Desc:
During a match, the account names of players who are eliminated will appear on the screen.
This setting allows you to replace your name with "Anonymous" in these messages for everyone who is not in your squad.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Note</>: People in the same "squad" (up to three other players on your team who may or may not be friends) will still be able to see your account name.
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: Players that are not in your squad will be able to see your account name.
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: Replace your name to players that are not in your squad with "Anonymous".
FortSetting.ShowSeasonLevel_Description:
During a match, your account name will show your Season level in the Elimination Feed.

This setting allows you to hide your Season level in those messages.

ON: Shows your Season level to players that are not in your squad.

OFF: Your Season level will be hidden for players that are not squad members.
FortSetting.DynamicResolution_Description: Dynamic 3D resolution occasionally increases the resolution that objects are rendered in game when your GPU is under used.
FortSetting.DynamicResOnlyWithTSR: Dynamic resolution is only available with TSR in the Anti-Aliasing and Super-Resolution settings.
FortSetting.DynamicResOnlyWithD3D12: Dynamic-resolution is only available on D3D12 Render Mode.
FortSetting.DynamicResOnlyWithBelowNative: Dynamic-resolution is only available when setting a 3D resolution lower than 100%.
FortSetting.DynamicResOnlyWithFrameRateLimit: Dynamic-resolution is only available when setting a Frame Rate Limit.
FortSetting.VisualEffectQuality_Description: Effects determines the quality of visual effects in game. Increasing this setting will increase the quality of visual effects, but can reduce performance.
FortSetting.HeadphoneMode_Description: Enable binaural audio.  Provides 3D audio spatialization, so you can hear the location of sounds more precisely, including above, below, and behind you. Recommended for use with stereo headphones only.
FortSetting.QuickWeaponToggle_Description:
Enable the experimental Quick Weapon action. When enabled, Quick Weapon replaces the Next Weapon button.

Press Quick Weapon to equip your primary item. Press one of the face buttons while pressing Quick Weapon to switch to one of the other item slots. You can press Quick Weapon and a face button simultaneously to swap to that item instantly, or hold the Quick Weapon button for as long as you like to get used to how the face buttons match up with the items in your inventory.

When this is enabled, Previous Weapon is replaced by Place Marker to make it easier to communicate with your squad. Or you can replace Previous Weapon with the action of your choice by customizing your controls in the Controller Customization tab.
FortSetting.InstantBoostWhenBuilding_Description: Enable this setting to ignore the boost ramp time when in build mode.  The boost speed will engage instantly when the stick is fully deflected when in build mode.
FortSetting.120fps_Description: Enable this to run the game at 120fps.
FortSetting.120fps_Description_Playstation: Enable this to run the game at 120fps. Please note that depending on your TV capabilities, your display resolution could be reduced to support this mode.
FortSetting.ShowFPS_Description: Enable this to show the frames per second. Use this to help gauge the effect of adjusting different video settings.
FortSetting.UseLegacyControls_Description: Enable to revert back to the legacy sensitivity behavior.
FortSetting.ShowVoiceIndicators_Description: Enables / Disables the notifications that appear when someone in your voice channel speaks.
FortSetting.GamepadFlickStick_Description:
Enables Flick Stick. When enabled, point the look stick on your controller in any direction to quickly flick the camera to face that direction. For example, pulling the stick back will flick behind you. Once the stick is tilted, rotate it to adjust your bearing.

Since this means you can no longer aim up and down with the stick, this requires Gyro Aiming to be enabled. With Flick Stick, it's best to have Gyro Aiming always active or set Look Stick Effect to ENABLES so that you can activate gyro at any time by engaging the stick.
FortSetting.AutoDownloadHighResTextures_Description:
Enables Fortnite to automatically download high resolution textures. Higher resolution textures make Fortnite look more detailed.

NOTE: Slower internet connections or devices with limited hard drive space may experience performance issues when the game is downloading high resolution textures. Turning this feature off may help improve performance and save disk space.

ON: Fortnite will automatically download high resolution textures.

OFF: Fortnite will not automatically download high resolution textures.
FortSetting.EasyLootGridEnabled_Description: Enables a scrollable widget where nearby items are shown. You can then pickup an item from there by clicking on it rather than having to click on the actual item widget on the scene.
FortSetting.EnergySavingIdle_Description: Enables energy savings when the game goes into idle mode in the FrontEnd. Idle mode starts after 30 seconds of inactivity.
FortSetting.EnergySavingFocus_Description: Enables energy savings when the game window is not the active window.
FortSetting.GyroV2AdvancedEnabled_Description: Enables or Disables Advanced Gyro Options.
FortSetting.GyroV2Enabled_Description: Enables or Disables Gyro Aiming. When active, turn your controller to turn the camera. This offers more precision than standard stick aiming, but doesn't have to replace it entirely. Usually players will still use the right stick for most camera control while using gyro aiming for finer adjustments that are difficult to do with a stick.
FortSetting.PlayerSurveys_Description: Enables or disables whether or not you are willing to receive periodic player surveys from Epic Games. Player surveys help guide the development of Fortnite, and generally you should not receive more than about one per month.
FortSetting.Vsync_Description: Enabling Vsync eliminates screen tearing by always rendering and presenting a full frame. Disabling Vsync can give higher frame rate and better input response, but can result in horizontal screen tearing. This feature only works if 'Window Mode' is set to 'Fullscreen'.
FortSetting.AutoCenter_Description: Enabling this setting will pull the camera towards the horizon when you're moving about and not aiming or firing. This can help new players who find themselves unintentionally staring at the ground or sky, or flick stick players who only have gyro aiming active in certain aim modes.
FortSetting.TouchAutoCenter_Description: Enabling this setting will pull the camera towards the horizon when you're moving about and not aiming or firing. This can help new players who find themselves unintentionally staring at the ground or sky.
FortSetting.WarningAboutEnableFlickStick_MessageMobi:
Flick Stick requires playing with a controller. Since flick stick also requires your mobile device's gyro for gyro aiming, enabling flick stick on mobile is only recommended for players who can mount their mobile device on their controller.

Flick stick can only turn the camera left and right. When flick stick is enabled, you can only look up and down using gyro controls.

In order to be able to look up and down at all times, we strongly recommend flick stick players set their Gyro Active Modes to ALWAYS or set Look Stick Effect to ENABLES. This lets you activate gyro aiming at any time by engaging the flick stick.
FortSetting.WarningAboutEnableFlickStick_Message:
Flick stick can only turn the camera left and right. When flick stick is enabled, you can only look up and down using gyro controls.

In order to be able to look up and down at all times, we strongly recommend flick stick players set their Gyro Active Modes to ALWAYS or set Look Stick Effect to ENABLES. This lets you activate gyro aiming at any time by engaging the flick stick.
FortSetting.ReleaseToFire_Description: For sniper rifles. Instead of firing when you press the touch look & fire button, fire sniper rifles when you release the look & fire button. This means you can line up the shot with one finger and then fire with that same finger by releasing. Other fire buttons will still fire on press.
FortSetting.PredownloadCosmetics_Description:
Fortnite streams in cosmetic textures as they are encountered in-game. By turning this feature on, you will pre-download all of these textures up front instead of as they are encountered. This uses much more disk space but allows Fortnite to look more detailed without costing any bandwidth. This can improve Fortnite's visual quality if you frequently play using a cellular connection.

No: Fortnite will uninstall any previously downloaded cosmetic textures and will not pre-download them in the future.

Yes: Fortnite will download and install all high-quality textures up front.
FortSetting.ParsleyIdle_Description: Fortnite will go into Sleep Mode after you are inactive for the selected number of minutes. This setting applies to all devices where you are signed in.
FortSetting.FlickForwardDeadZone_Description: Forward angle where pointing the flick stick won't flick the camera (degrees).
FortSetting.FrameRateLimit_Description: Frame rate limit sets the highest frame rate that is allowed. Set this lower for a more consistent frame rate or higher for the best experience on faster machines. You may need to disable Vsync to reach high frame rates.
FortSetting.EnableDLSSFrameGeneration_Description: Generates an additional frame for each rendered frame. Requires an NVIDIA 40 series RTX GPU
FortSetting.ShowFriendInvitesPush_DescriptionMobile: Get notified when you have a new friend invite.
FortSetting.ShowPartyInvitesPush_DescriptionMobile: Get notified when you have a new party invite.
FortSetting.AutorunLockZonePreference_Description:
Gives the user the ability to keep running without requiring constant input.
Activate the Auto Run functionality by dragging your finger over the Auto Run Lock Zone while moving forward.

<strong>OFF</>: The Auto Run Lock Zone functionality is disabled.
<strong>CUSTOM</>: The Auto Run Lock Zone can be positioned manually through the HUD Layout Tool.
<strong>FIXED</>: The Auto Run Lock Zone is positioned above the move stick.
FortSetting.AutorunLockZonePreference_NoCustom_Descr:
Gives the user the ability to keep running without requiring constant input.
Activate the Auto Run functionality by dragging your finger over the Auto Run Lock Zone while moving forward.

<strong>OFF</>: The Auto Run Lock Zone functionality is disabled.
<strong>ON</>: The Auto Run Lock Zone is enabled and positioned above the move stick.
FortSetting.GlobalIllumination_Description:
Global Illumination controls the quality of ambient lighting.

The 'Lumen High' and 'Lumen Epic' options are much higher quality, but can reduce performance.

Off: Ambient lighting is unshadowed.

Ambient Occlusion: Lower quality ambient lighting with darkened corners.

Lumen High/Epic: High quality real-time global illumination.
FortSetting.TurnOnNotifications_Description:
Go to your device settings to turn notifications on.

When enabled, you will be notified when content downloads have completed, friend and party invites, new seasons, limited time events, announcements and promotions. Configure these at any time here in Fortnite Settings.
FortSetting.TurnOnNotificationsAndroid_Description:
Go to your device settings to turn notifications on.

When enabled, you will be notified when content downloads have completed, friend and party invites, new seasons, limited time events, announcements and promotions. Configure these at any time here in Fortnite Settings.

In order to download updates while using other apps notifications must be allowed.
FortSetting.DualShock4RequiredForGyro: Gyro Aiming on Windows requires a DualShock 4 (PS4) or DualSense (PS5) controller connected by USB.
FortSetting.GyroAccelMultiplier_Description: Gyro aiming multiplier when you're making fast movements with the gyro (at or above the Max Threshold). When you're moving slowly (at or below the Min Threshold), no multiplier is applied. Between the Min and Max Thresholds, your aim speed will be increased in proportion to how far it is in-between those thresholds.
FortSetting.GyroControlsRequiredForFlickStick: Gyro aiming must be enabled to use flick stick.
FortSetting.GyroCheatSensitivity_Description: Gyro aiming sensitivity. Choose 1 for the camera to turn the same amount as the controller (unless using the Legacy acceleration mode).
FortSetting.GyroV2Sensitivity_Description: Gyro aiming sensitivity. Choose 1 for the camera to turn the same amount as the controller, 2 for the camera to turn twice as much, etc. The amount the camera turns is increased by your Acceleration settings and decreased as you zoom in with long-range weapons. You can toggle zoom scaling or change your sensitivity for different tools and aim modes by enabling Advanced Gyro Options below.
FortSetting.GyroV2ScopedSensitivity_Description: Gyro sensitivity multiplier while aiming with scoped weapons.
FortSetting.GyroV2TargetingSensitivity_Description: Gyro sensitivity multiplier while aiming your weapon.
FortSetting.GyroV2BuildingToolSensitivity_Descriptio: Gyro sensitivity multiplier while in build mode.
FortSetting.GyroV2EditingToolSensitivity_Description: Gyro sensitivity multiplier while in edit mode.
FortSetting.GyroV2HarvestingToolSensitivity_Descript: Gyro sensitivity multiplier while using the Pickaxe.
FortSetting.GyroCheatScopedSensitivity_Description: Gyro sensitivity while targeting with scoped weapons.
FortSetting.GyroCheatHarvestingToolSensitivity_Descr: Gyro sensitivity while using the Pickaxe.
FortSetting.EnableHardwareRayTracing_Description: Hardware Ray Tracing enables higher quality Lumen global illumination and reflections, but can reduce performance.
FortSetting.GyroTighteningThreshold_Description: Helps keep your aim steady by reducing gyro aiming speed when your controller is turning very slowly. The threshold is how fast the controller needs to turn to disable this tightening effect (in degrees per second), and this effect can be disabled entirely by setting the threshold to 0. Gyro Deadzone is added to this threshold so that if both are enabled, Tightening provides a smooth transition out of the deadzone.
FortSetting.HideOtherPlayerNames_Name: Hide Other Display Names During Regular Gameplay
FortSetting.AnonymousMode_Name: Hide Your Display Name During Regular Gameplay
FortSetting.HideSocialName_Name: Hide Your Linked Social Account Names
FortSetting.HideSocialName_Description: Hides linked social media accounts from friends.
FortSetting.EnableNanite_Description: High-end geometry rendering through Nanite which improves geometry detail, but can lower framerate. Virtual Shadow Maps will be used when Nanite is enabled for higher quality shadowing.
FortSetting.MeshQuality_Description: Higher geometry settings gives objects a more detailed shape. Increasing this setting will make objects more detailed, but can reduce performance.
FortSetting.TextureQuality_Description_Default: Higher textures settings give flat objects a more detailed appearance. Increasing this setting will make objects more detailed, but can reduce performance.
FortSetting.TextureQuality_Description_NoHighMips:
Higher textures settings give flat objects a more detailed appearance. Increasing this setting will make objects more detailed, but can reduce performance.

High quality textures are not installed. They can be downloaded from the Epic Games Launcher in the Fortnite Installation Options.
FortSetting.ContinuousFire_Description: Holding the fire button will fire semi-automatic weapons repeatedly.
FortSetting.FlickTime_Description: How long a Flick Stick flick takes.
FortSetting.CameraResetTime_Description: How long it takes to reset the camera position when pressing the Reset Camera button.
FortSetting.QuickWeaponDiamondDelay_Description:
How long the Quick Weapon button must be held for the Quick Weapon diamond to appear on the HUD. This delay only affects the visible HUD. It doesn't add any delay to using Quick Weapon itself. If you press and release the desired Quick Weapon combo in less than this time, the diamond won't show up on the HUD, but your equipped item will still change correctly.

Set this to its maximum value to never show the Quick Weapon diamond.
FortSetting.SlideButtonHoldTime_Description: How long to hold the slide button to start sliding.
FortSetting.AimAssistStrength_Description: How much aim assist to apply.  A setting of 0% will disable aim assist.  Lowering this setting is not recommended.
FortSetting.GyroSimpleSteadying_Description:
How much filtering to apply to gyro aiming when you're trying to keep your aim still or move it very little.

This slider controls the strength of Smoothing and Tightening filters, as well as whether to try to filter out controller vibration if Vibration is enabled in the Controller Options tab. More control over these filters is available under Advanced Gyro Options.
FortSetting.TouchLookAccelerationMultiplier_Descript: How much look acceleration to apply.
FortSetting.LookHorizontalSpeedAds_Description: How quickly your view rotates left and right while aiming down sights.
FortSetting.LookHorizontalSpeed_Description: How quickly your view rotates left and right.
FortSetting.LookVerticalSpeedAds_Description: How quickly your view rotates up and down while aiming down sights.
FortSetting.LookVerticalSpeed_Description: How quickly your view rotates up and down.
FortSetting.LookSensitivityPresetAds_Description: How quickly your view rotates while aiming down sights (ADS).
FortSetting.GyroV2SpaceHandheld_Description:
How the motion inputs are converted to camera Yaw and Pitch rotations when playing in handheld mode.

LOCAL space means rotation is detected from the device's point of view, and will work the same whether you're lying down, sitting up, in zero gravity, etc. This means it's often the best option for handheld gaming.

PLAYER space will detect motion relative to the direction of gravity, giving you the most freedom of movement and the most natural camera control when you're playing with a controller in front of a fixed screen.
FortSetting.GyroV2SpaceSwitch_Description:
How the motion inputs are converted to camera Yaw and Pitch rotations when playing with a Pro Controller or Joy-Cons detached from the console.

LOCAL space means rotation is detected from the device's point of view, and will work the same whether you're lying down, sitting up, in zero gravity, etc. This means it's often the best option for handheld gaming.

PLAYER space will detect motion relative to the direction of gravity, giving you the most freedom of movement and the most natural camera control when you're playing with a controller in front of a fixed screen.
FortSetting.GyroV2Space_Description:
How the motion inputs are converted to camera Yaw and Pitch rotations.

LOCAL space means rotation is detected from the device's point of view, and will work the same whether you're lying down, sitting up, in zero gravity, etc. This means it's often the best option for handheld gaming.

PLAYER space will detect motion relative to the direction of gravity, giving you the most freedom of movement and the most natural camera control when you're playing with a controller in front of a fixed screen.
FortSetting.FilterControllerVibrationFromGyro_Descri: If controller vibration is enabled, add a narrow filter to reduce camera vibration. This can add a tiny bit of input latency to gyro aiming. This filter is automatically disabled if the Vibration option is disabled in the Controller Options tab.
FortSetting.CrossplayPreference_Description: If enabled you can participate in parties and game modes with other platforms. If disabled, some game modes will be unavailable, and others may have Limited Pools with longer queue times, lower match populations, or higher latency.
FortSetting.HoldToSwapPickup_Description: If enabled, current weapon can be swapped with pickup on the ground by holding use.
FortSetting.GyroButtonHoldTime_Description: If the Gyro Modifier button is shared with a short-press action, this is how long the button needs to be held to skip the short-press action.
FortSetting.LicensedAudioTreatment_Description:
If you are a content creator, you can select this option to avoid playing licensed music from audio sources and also avoid viewing copyrighted videos from any video player. This setting does not apply to event playlists that feature content that is licensed like concerts.

<strong>Play</>: The audio is played normally (Default).

<strong>Mute Others</>: When other players play audio sources with licensed audio, the audio will be muted.

<strong>Mute All</>: All sources containing licensed audio will be muted if you or anyone plays them.
FortSetting.UseGPUCrashDebugging_Description: If you experience crashes consider enabling GPU Crash Debugging to help the developers track down the root causes of your issues. Enabling this feature comes at a small performance cost.
FortSetting.GyroV2JoyConSelection_Description: If you're holding a Joy-Con in each hand, choose which Joy-Con will be used for gyro aiming.
FortSetting.IgnoreGamepadInput_Description: Ignore all controller input.  If you are using a input remapping tool, remapping controller input to keyboard keys, and don't want the game to also receive the controller input.
FortSetting.GyroDeadZone_Description: Ignore gyro input below this threshold (degrees per second). This can make it impossible to track a distant or slow-moving target depending on your sensitivity settings, so it's usually preferable to try stabilize your aim using the Smoothing or Tightening options above before resorting to this.
FortSetting.FilterMatureLanguage_Desc:
In Fortnite Battle Royale players can text chat with friends in their squad when in the lobby.
In Fortnite Save The World players can text chat with friends in the lobby, and with any other players in a private or public match.
This option lets you filter mature language in the chat, both that you send and receive from others.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: Mature language in text chat will be filtered and replaced with heart symbols.
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: Mature language can appear in text chat.
FortSetting.LookStickDeadZone_Description: Increase or decrease the area surrounding the stick that we ignore input from.  Setting this value too low may result in the camera continuing to move even after removing your finger from the stick.
FortSetting.MoveStickDeadZone_Description: Increase or decrease the area surrounding the stick that we ignore input from.  Setting this value too low may result in the character continuing to move even after removing your finger from the stick.
FortSetting.GyroCheatVert_Description: Increase or decrease your vertical sensitivity relative to your horizontal sensitivity.
FortSetting.XeSS is Disabled: Intel XeSS is disabled in the Anti Aliasing & Super Resolution setting.
FortSetting.XeSS_Description: Intel Xe Super Sampling (XeSS) technology uses AI to deliver more performance with exceptional image quality.
FortSetting.GyroV2InvertPitch_Description: Invert or disable the Pitch axis.
FortSetting.GyroV2InvertRoll_Description: Invert or disable the Roll axis (when using LOCAL gyro space)
FortSetting.GyroV2InvertYaw_Description: Invert or disable the Yaw axis.
FortSetting.FlickDeadZone_Description: It's better for the flick to only be triggered towards the outer edge of the stick's range, because that will give a more accurate measure of your intended angle. So this DeadZone is how far between the Look Stick DeadZone below and the outer edge that flick stick should actually be triggered.
FortSetting.UseLatency_Description: Latency Markers are needed for the latency debug hud. Requires an NVIDIA video card and the latest drivers.
FortSetting.LatencyMarkersDisabledBecauseOfFrameGene: Latency markers are required when NVIDIA DLSS Frame Generation is enabled.
FortSetting.Logout_Description: Logout from this account from Fortnite.
FortSetting.Lumen is disabled: Lumen GI or Reflections must be enabled.
FortSetting.LumenUnavailableInGameMode: Lumen is not available in this game mode
FortSetting.ShowFriendRequest_Description: Manages notifications for friend requests. They will still appear in the social menu.
FortSetting.ShowFriendRequest_DescriptionMobile:
Manages notifications for friend requests. They will still appear in the social menu.

      <Icon.Warning></> Also affects <strong>mobile push notifications</>.
FortSetting.ShowPartyInvite_DescriptionMobile:
Manages notifications for party invites.

      <Icon.Warning></> Also affects <strong>mobile push notifications</>.
FortSetting.ShowNotifications_Description: Manages social notifications such as party invites and friend requests.
FortSetting.ShowNotifications_DescriptionMobile:
Manages social notifications such as party invites and friend requests.

      <Icon.Warning></> Also affects <strong>mobile push notifications</>.
FortSetting.MouseSensitivityMultiplierForAircraft_Na: Mouse Sensitivity Multiplier For Aircraft Steering
FortSetting.DLSS_Description: NVIDIA DLSS (Deep Learning Super Sampling). NVIDIA DLSS uses deep learning to render highly detailed images using fewer pixels, boosting your frame rates so you can maximize your graphics settings and output resolution.  DLSS requires an NVIDIA RTX graphics card.
FortSetting.DLSSFrameGenerationDisabledHardwareSched: NVIDIA DLSS Frame Generation is disabled because hardware-accelerated GPU scheduling is not enabled in Windows. Please enable hardware-accelerated GPU scheduling to enable NVIDIA DLSS Frame Generation. This option can be found in the Windows Settings -> System -> Display -> Graphics Settings.
FortSetting.DLSSFrameGenerationDisabledDriverOutOfDa: NVIDIA DLSS Frame Generation is disabled because your graphics driver is out of date. Please update your graphics driver to enable NVIDIA DLSS Frame Generation.
FortSetting.DLSSFrameGenerationDisabledOperatingSyst: NVIDIA DLSS Frame Generation is disabled because your operating system is out of date. Please update your operating system to enable NVIDIA DLSS Frame Generation.
FortSetting.DLSS is Disabled: NVIDIA DLSS is disabled in the Anti Aliasing & Super Resolution setting.
FortSetting.UseLatency2_Description: NVIDIA Reflex Low Latency reduces system latency in GPU bound scenarios. Requires an NVIDIA video card and the latest drivers.
FortSetting.LatencyTweakOffDisabledBecauseOfFrameGen: NVIDIA Reflex is required when NVIDIA DLSS Frame Generation is enabled.
FortSetting.CanDisplayMyUserName_Name: Non-Squad Members Can See Your Name
FortSetting.AutoHideBuildingMaterials_Description: Only show building materials on the HUD in build mode or when obtaining materials
FortSetting.TouchFireMode_Description: Opens the Fire Mode selection screen
FortSetting.InvitePermissions_Description:
Pick who can send you Friend Requests.

      <Icon.Warning></> This <strong>may</> remove pending invites.
FortSetting.3DAudioDisabled_OSOverridden:
Please check your system settings to enable or disable 3D Audio.
This setting does not reflect the current state of 3D Audio as Fortnite disables the 3D Headphones mode in favor of the 3D Sound solution provided by your Operating System.
FortSetting.RestartConfirmationDescription: Please restart the game for all changes to take effect.
FortSetting.WarningAboutToUseAdvancedOptions_Message: Please use caution when changing the advanced options.  Incorrect settings can have a negative effect on your ability to aim.
FortSetting.PostProcessingQuality_Description: Post Processing effects include Motion Blur, Depth of Field and Bloom. Increasing this setting improves the quality of post process effects, but can reduce performance.
FortSetting.PreferredItemSlotsPage_Description:
Preferred Item Slots allows you to assign a preferred inventory slot for a weapon or item type. On pick up, your preferred item or weapon type will be placed into its preferred inventory slot.

Press Configure to customize your inventory slots.
FortSetting.UseAdvancedOptions_Description: Provides additional fine-tuning of the look and aim sensitivities.  Advanced options will be used instead of the "Look Sensitivity" and "Aim Sensitivity (ADS)" basic settings.  <strong>Use with caution!</>
FortSetting.GraphicsQualityPresets_Description: Quality Preset allows you to adjust multiple video options at once. Try a few options to see what fits your preference and device's performance.
FortSetting.GyroTrackballDecay_Description: Rate of slow-down for gyro trackball (only affects behavior of the TRACKBALL options for Gyro Button X and Gyro Button Y).
FortSetting.GyroV2VerticalMultiplier_Description: Reduce vertical sensitivity by moving the slider to the left, or reduce horizontal sensitivity by moving the slider to the right.
FortSetting.WindingSpeedScaledByZoom_Description: Reduces flick stick's rotation speed automatically depending on how much you're zoomed in. This can help steady surveying the landscape while sniping, for example. This doesn't affect the flick itself when you first engage the stick.
FortSetting.GyroSensitivityScaledByZoom_Description: Reduces your aiming sensitivity automatically depending on how much you're zoomed in. This can help steady your aim with long range weapons.
FortSetting.Reflections_Description:
Reflection quality determines the resolution and accuracy of reflections.

The 'Lumen High' and 'Lumen Epic' options are much higher quality, but can reduce performance.

Off: Reflections are turned off.

Screen Space: Calculates reflections based only on what is currently shown on the screen.

Lumen High/Epic: High quality real-time ray traced reflections.
FortSetting.MouseSensitivityMultiplierForAircraft_De: Regular mouse sensitivity settings are multiplied by this value when steering an aircraft by mouse
FortSetting.RequirePinToAddEpicFriends_Name: Require PIN to add Epic Friends
FortSetting.SetupAdvancedToMatchBasic_Description: Resets the advanced options to match the currently selected "Look Sensitivity" and "Aim Sensitivity (ADS)" from the non-advanced options.
FortSetting.ToggleDoubleTapAutorun_Description:
Run forward without having to hold the move stick.
Activate the Auto Run functionality by tapping the move stick twice.
FortSetting.AutoMulchCollection_Name: Save The World - Automatic Recycle / Retire
FortSetting.FortniteCredits_Description: See everyone who contributed to the making of Fortnite.
FortSetting.SelectAndroidStore_Description: Select a Checkout to use when making real money purchases.
FortSetting.MobileFPSType_Description: Select a desired framerate. Use this to fine tune performance on your device.
FortSetting.GyroYawAxis_Description: Selects the axis used for Yaw rotation with motion controls.
FortSetting.TouchInteractMode_Description:
Selects touch interaction mode.

<strong>Off</>: Touch interactions disabled.
FortSetting.RenderingAPI_Description:
Selects which low-level rendering mode to use.

DirectX 11 is the older graphics API.

Performance is a mode that offers significant performance gains by disabling most rendering features to reduce memory usage and lighten the load on CPU and GPU.

DirectX 12 is a newer graphics API and may offer a performance increase over DirectX 11. It is required to enable Nanite (which dynamically and highly efficiently scales meshes in the environment) and Lumen (which uses multiple ray-tracing methods to solve global illumination and reflections).
FortSetting.FortReleaseVersion_Description: Selects which release version you want to use for determining what features are enabled (i.e. 15.20, 15.30, 16.00, etc).
FortSetting.MatchmakingRegion_Description: Selects which server you wish to connect to. Servers that are closer to you will generally have better performance. Selecting 'Auto' picks the server with the best connection.
FortSetting.GyroSensitivity_Description: Sensitivity of Motion Controls while not targeting.
FortSetting.GyroScopedSensitivity_Description: Sensitivity of Motion Controls while targeting with scoped weapons.
FortSetting.GyroTargetingSensitivity_Description: Sensitivity of Motion Controls while targeting.
FortSetting.GyroHarvestingToolSensitivity_Descriptio: Sensitivity of Motion Controls while using the Pickaxe.
FortSetting.GyroV2Button_Description:
Set a button to pause gyro aiming or change gyro behavior while this button is pressed. This lets you reset your controller position without unintentionally turning the camera. Gyro aiming will be paused while this button is held, but you can still use the button's regular action with a short press.

You can also set Gyro Modifier buttons in the controller customization tab.

You can set this button to do something other than pause gyro, such as enable or invert it, under Advanced Gyro Options.
FortSetting.TimeLimitsActionDescription: Set limits for the total time your child spends in Fortnite and Unreal Editor for Fortnite (UEFN).
FortSetting.SafeZone_Description: Set the UI safe zone for the platform.
FortSetting.TouchDragSensitivity_Description: Set the sensitivity of touch and drag. With higher settings the camera will move faster when dragging to look around.
FortSetting.VoiceChat_ExpandedSettings_Description:
Sets scope of other players you wish to voice chat with.

<strong>Everybody</>: You can hear everyone and can also talk to them by using a microphone.

<strong>Friends and Teammates</>: You can hear friends and teammates and can also talk to them by using a microphone.

<strong>Friends Only</>: You can hear friends and can also talk to them by using a microphone.

<strong>Nobody</>: Epic voice chat is disabled.
FortSetting.VoiceChat_VRR_ExpandedSettings_Descripti:
Sets scope of other players you wish to voice chat with. Turning on chat also turns on voice reporting.

<strong>Everybody</>: You can hear everyone and can also talk to them by using a microphone.

<strong>Friends and Teammates</>: You can hear friends and teammates and can also talk to them by using a microphone.

<strong>Friends Only</>: You can hear friends and can also talk to them by using a microphone.

<strong>Off</>: Voice chat and voice reporting is off.

<strong>About voice reporting</>
When voice chat is on, voice reporting stores voice chat audio on each participant's device on a rolling five-minute basis, which will be sent to Epic Games only if a participant reports a violation. Voice reporting is usually on, except in parties formed among friends where all players prefer voice reporting off. You can see if voice reporting is currently on or off in the Sidebar. Voice reporting is always on for players under 18.

See the voice reporting setting for more details and options.
FortSetting.ToggleSprint_Description: Sets sprint to be an on/off toggle or a hold to sprint. When on, sprint is set to an on/off toggle with one press.
FortSetting.ToggleTargeting_Description_Mobile: Sets targeting to be an on/off toggle or a hold when using a controller or other non-touch devices. When on, the targeting control will be an on/off toggle. Turning off sets the targeting control to be a hold.
FortSetting.ToggleTargetingTouch_Description: Sets targeting to be an on/off toggle or a hold when using touch controls. When on, the targeting control will be an on/off toggle. Turning off sets the targeting control to be a hold.
FortSetting.ToggleTargeting_Description: Sets targeting to be an on/off toggle or a hold. When on, the targeting control will be an on/off toggle. Turning off sets the targeting control to be a hold
FortSetting.RudderDeadZone_Description: Sets the Dead Zone of the foot controller.
FortSetting.RudderMaxThrottle_Description: Sets the max throttle point of the foot controller.
FortSetting.GamepadBuildingMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for controller sensitivity when in build mode. 1x will have no change when in build mode. Lower settings will have more slow down when in build mode, and higher settings will increase sensitivity when in build mode.
FortSetting.GamepadEditModeMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for controller sensitivity when in edit mode. 1x will have no change when in edit mode. Lower settings will have more slow down when in edit mode, and higher settings will increase sensitivity when in edit mode.
FortSetting.MouseBuildingMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for mouse sensitivity when building. 100% will have no slow down or increase when building.
FortSetting.MouseEditingMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for mouse sensitivity when editing. 100% will have no slow down or increase when editing.
FortSetting.GamepadTargetingMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for reducing controller sensitivity when targeting. 100% will have no slow down when targeting. Lower settings will have more slow down when targeting.
FortSetting.GamepadScopedMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for reducing controller sensitivity when using a scope. 100% will have no slow down when using a scope. Lower settings will have more slow down when scoped.
FortSetting.MouseTargetingMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for reducing mouse sensitivity when targeting. 100% will have no slow down when targeting. Lower settings will have more slow down when targeting.
FortSetting.MouseScopedMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for reducing mouse sensitivity when using a scope. 100% will have no slow down when using a scope. Lower settings will have more slow down when scoped.
FortSetting.TouchDragTargetingSensitivity_Descriptio: Sets the modifier for reducing touch and drag sensitivity when targeting. 100% will have no slow down when targeting. Lower settings will have more slow down when targeting.
FortSetting.TouchDragScopedSensitivity_Description: Sets the modifier for reducing touch and drag sensitivity when using a scope. 100% will have no slow down when using a scope. Lower settings will have more slow down when scoped.
FortSetting.TouchBuildingMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for touch sensitivity when in build mode. 100% will have no change when in build mode. Lower settings will have more slow down when in build mode, and higher settings will increase sensitivity when in build mode.
FortSetting.TouchEditModeMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for touch sensitivity when in edit mode. 100% will have no change when in edit mode. Lower settings will have more slow down when in edit mode, and higher settings will increase sensitivity when in edit mode.
FortSetting.ControllerLookSensitivityPitch_Descripti: Sets the sensitivity of the controller stick's vertical (y) axis. With higher settings the camera will move faster when looking up and down with the controller stick.
FortSetting.ControllerLookSensitivityYaw_Description: Sets the sensitivity of the controller sticks' horizontal (x) axis. With higher settings the camera will move faster when looking left and right with the controller stick.
FortSetting.MouseSensitivityYaw_Description: Sets the sensitivity of the mouse's horizontal (x) axis. With higher settings the camera will move faster when looking left and right with the mouse.
FortSetting.MouseSensitivityPitch_Description: Sets the sensitivity of the mouse's vertical (y) axis. With higher settings the camera will move faster when looking up and down with the mouse.
FortSetting.HUDScale_DescriptionMobile: Sets the size of heads up display (HUD) elements when using a controller or a Keyboard and mouse. 100% will show the default HUD size. Lower the settings will make HUD elements smaller.
FortSetting.HUDScale_Description: Sets the size of heads up display (HUD) elements. 100% will show the default HUD size. Lower settings will make HUD elements smaller.
FortSetting.SoundQuality_Description: Sets the sound quality. 'High' quality sounds better, but may decrease performance.
FortSetting.Setting Enabled: Setting Disabled when Performance is not selected.
FortSetting.Setting Disabled: Setting Disabled when Performance is selected.
FortSetting.ResolutionScale_Warning: Setting the 3D resolution to a higher value than the device's capacity may impact performance.
FortSetting.ResolutionScale_LowValue_Warning: Setting the 3D resolution to values below 10% may negatively impact game playability.
FortSetting.Shadows_Description: Shadow quality determines the resolution and view distance of dynamic shadows. Shadows improve visual quality and give better depth perception, but can reduce performance.  Virtual Shadow Maps will be used when Nanite is enabled for even higher quality.
FortSetting.SocialPrivacy_ShareActivity_Description:
Share Activity allows you to share your play history and online presence with the Fortnite community.

ON: When turned on, your online presence will be publicly visible and the games that you are playing will be posted to your Creator page under the Shared Play History section.

OFF: When turned off, your online presence will not be publicly visible. Also, gameplay that occurs when this option is off will not be posted publicly to your Creator Page.
FortSetting.GyroActiveCheatMode_Description: Should gyro always be active, or only when aiming/firing? If always active, it's good to set something else to disable gyro.
FortSetting.AutoImportFriends_Description: Should we auto import platform friends?
FortSetting.UseBothQuickbarsLayout_Description: Show both Quickbars at the same time.  When off, only the active quickbar will be displayed (combat or building)
FortSetting.ContextTutorial_Description: Show helpful tips for new players.
FortSetting.MapPickupDotRarity_Description: Show pickup indicators for ingredients, ammo, and building materials on the map at or above the specified rarity
FortSetting.STW_ShowGrass_Description: Shows grass in the game, which can reduce performance on slower machines. Disable to hide grass and improve performance.
FortSetting.FullRangeTest_Description: Shows the full grayscale range calibration UI.
FortSetting.GyroSmoothingThreshold_Description: Smooth gyro input that's below this threshold (degrees per second). Set to 0 to disable smoothing entirely. Gyro Deadzone is added to this threshold so that the Deadzone setting never cancels out your Smoothing Threshold.
FortSetting.UnsupportedD3D12: Software or hardware requirements are not met. DirectX 12 requires a newer version of Windows 10 (newer than version 1909.1350) or Windows 11 with support for DirectX 12 Agility SDK, a dedicated graphics card with advanced shading features, and the latest graphics drivers.
FortSetting.UserInterfaceParallax_Description: Some menus like the Item Shop may have parallax effects. Disable this setting for those effects to remain static.
FortSetting.MotionBlur_Description: Some people are very sensitive to motion blur. Disable this effect to prevent nausea or keep it enabled to get more fluent animations.
FortSetting.FlickStickDisablesStandardStickSettings: Standard stick settings are disabled because Flick Stick is enabled in the Touch & Motion tab.
FortSetting.ShowMarketingInvitesPush_DescriptionMobi: Stay up to date with what is happening in Fortnite! Get notified about new seasons, limited time events, announcements and promotions.
FortSetting.StopRenderingInBackground_Description: Stop rendering when game window is not focused when possible. Frees up GPU resources for other applications.
FortSetting.SuppressMusicInJam_Name: Suppress My Emote Music to Hear Jam Tracks
FortSetting.AllowEmoteBeatSyncing_Name: Synchronize My Emotes to Jam Tracks
FortSetting.TapToInteractMobile_Name: Tap to Search / Interact With Controller
FortSetting.TSR is Disabled: Temporal Super Resolution is disabled in the Anti Aliasing & Super Resolution setting.
FortSetting.TSR is Enabled: Temporal Super Resolution is enabled in the Anti Aliasing & Super Resolution setting. Use the Temporal Super Resolution setting to control the 3D resolution rendered every frame.
FortSetting.LumenRequiresD3D12: The 'Rendering Mode' setting must be set to 'DirectX 12' in order to enable Lumen.
FortSetting.NaniteRequiresD3D12: The 'Rendering Mode' setting must be set to 'DirectX 12' in order to enable Nanite.
FortSetting.KeyboardMovementBackwardDiagonal_Descrip: The angle to run when entering a backward diagonal with keyboard.
FortSetting.KeyboardMovementForwardDiagonal_Descript: The angle to run when entering a forward diagonal with keyboard.
FortSetting.KeyboardMovementStrafeDiagonal_Descripti: The angle to run when strafing with keyboard.
FortSetting.EditButtonHoldTime_Description: The duration to hold the button for entering Edit Mode.
FortSetting.FOVMaximum_Description: The maximum allowed Field of View (FOV) during gameplay.
FortSetting.FOVMinimum_Description: The minimum allowed Field of View (FOV) during gameplay.
FortSetting.TriggerHapticsStartPosition_Description: The start position of the Adaptive Trigger effects.
FortSetting.TriggerHapticsStrength_Description: The strength of the Adaptive Trigger effect.
FortSetting.GyroAccelMaxThreshold_Description: The threshold at and above which the full Fast Multiplier is applied (degrees per second).
FortSetting.GyroAccelMinThreshold_Description: The threshold at and below which no acceleration is applied (degrees per second).
FortSetting.LookBoostAccelerationTimeAds_Description: The time it takes to reach the boost speed when the controller's right stick is fully deflected while aiming down sights.  A setting of 0.0 seconds will cause the boost to kick in instantly.
FortSetting.LookBoostAccelerationTime_Description: The time it takes to reach the boost speed when the controller's right stick is fully deflected.  A setting of 0.0 seconds will cause the boost to kick in instantly.
FortSetting.LookEaseTime_Description: The time it takes to reach the expected look rotation speed after applying initial input to the controller's right stick.  This allows for small view adjustments by tapping the stick.  Set to 0.0 seconds to disable the dampening.
FortSetting.ReportPerfStats_Description: This feature enables the upload of detailed performance stats for the next several matches, or until you exit the game.
FortSetting.LowInputLatencyMode_Description: This feature greatly <strong>reduces input lag</>, but may have a minor impact on framerate in some situations.
FortSetting.GyroV2TouchMode_Description: This lets you activate or deactivate gyro aiming by touching the look region of your screen, regardless of your Active Mode settings.
FortSetting.GyroV2StickMode_Description:
This lets you force gyro aiming off or on by using the look stick on your controller, regardless of your Active Mode settings.

Setting to DISABLES can make it easier to adjust your camera with the look stick without being affected by controller movements. Setting to ENABLES can be useful with Flick Stick, giving you a way to activate gyro controls at any time so you can still look up and down.
FortSetting.MatureLanguageFilter_Description:
This option lets you filter mature language in text chat, both that you send and receive from others, by replacing mature language with heart symbols

In Fortnite Battle Royale players can text chat with friends and other party members when in the lobby.

In Fortnite Save The World players can text chat with friends in the lobby, and with any other players in a private or public match.
FortSetting.AllowPersonalizationExperience_Descripti:
This setting allows the messages you receive about Fortnite experiences to be personalized. Examples of these types of messages would be announcements or recommendations for Fortnite in-game events we think you might like.

<strong>ON</>: Messages about Fortnite experiences can be personalized

<strong>OFF</>: Messages about Fortnite experiences will not be personalized
FortSetting.AllowPersonalizationPurchase_Description:
This setting allows the messages you receive about Fortnite purchase offers to be personalized. Examples of these types of messages would be announcements or recommendations about shop items and other purchases in Fortnite we think you might like.

<strong>ON</>: Messages about Fortnite purchase offers can be personalized.

<strong>OFF</>: Messages about Fortnite purchase offers will not be personalized.
FortSetting.AllowDiscoveryPersonalization_Descriptio:
This setting enables you to receive personalized game experience recommendations when using the Discover tab.

<strong>ON</>: Recommendations you receive in your Discover tab will be personalized.

<strong>OFF</>: Recommendations you receive in your Discover tab will not be personalized.
FortSetting.SocialStatus_PartyJoinability_Descriptio:
This setting is for how players join your party.

<strong>Invite Only</>: You or someone in your party have to invite players or accept their requests to join in order for them to join the party.

<strong>Friends</>: Players on your friends list and friends of party members will be able to join your party at any time.

NOTE: A party can always be joined via invite.
FortSetting.PreferredFilledMatchAudioChannel_Descrip:
This setting only applies when you choose to play a mode while already in a party and have Fill turned ON.

Fill is when your empty slots are filled with random players. Note: this setting does not apply when playing a game mode by yourself.

<strong>GAME:</>

By selecting this Game setting your voice chat will leave the Party Channel and automatically be switched into the Game Channel and you will be able to chat with the random players on your team.

<strong>PARTY:</>

By selecting this Party setting you will stay in the Party Voice Channel and will have to manually switch to the Game Channel in order to chat with the random players on your team.
FortSetting.FlickSmoothingThreshold_Description: Threshold above which no smoothing will be applied to rotations (rotations per second).
FortSetting.TimeLimitsActionWarning: Time Limits set for your device or console operate independently of your Fortnite Time Limits, and may further limit allowed time on that device.
FortSetting.QuickWeaponOnPress_Description:
To select your primary weapon, press and release the Quick Weapon button without pressing one of the other weapon buttons. By default, the primary weapon is only selected after releasing the Quick Weapon button, and not the instant it is pressed. This is to help players learn to press button combos to select other weapons. But for those who want to switch to their primary weapon as quickly as possible, enable this setting. This will equip your primary weapon the instant Quick Weapon is pressed.

This has no effect on selecting slots 2-5, which already happen the instant the corresponding button is pressed.
FortSetting.GyroV2AimAssist_Description: Trigger aim assist when gyro aiming.
FortSetting.STW_AutoEquipBetterItems_Description: Turn auto equip better items on/off. When on, better items will automatically be equipped when they are received.
FortSetting.ShadowPlayHighlights_Description: Turns NVIDIA highlights on/off. When on, NVIDIA highlights are automatically recorded for certain game events, like winning, getting eliminations, or being eliminated. This feature requires specific NVIDIA hardware.
FortSetting.QuickEdit_Description: Turns Quick Edit on/off. When on, editing a base structure will implement a basic edit based on player orientation and where they are looking at the structure. When using on an already edited structure, it will reset the piece back to the base structure.
FortSetting.SimpleBuild_Description: Turns Simple Build on/off. When on, building pieces are chosen based on build mode (Traversal or Defense) and view direction.
FortSetting.AimAssist_Description: Turns aim assist on/off. When on, this helps attract your aim towards enemy players when using a controller.
FortSetting.TouchAimAssist_Description: Turns aim assist on/off. When on, this helps attract your aim towards enemy players when using a controller.
FortSetting.InvertPitchForAircraftSecondary_Descript: Turns aircraft mouse steering inversion on/off. When on, moving the mouse forward will pitch the aircraft down.
FortSetting.InvertPitchForAircraftPrimary_Descriptio: Turns aircraft steering inversion on/off. When on, pressing forward will pitch the aircraft down.
FortSetting.AutoOpenDoors_Description: Turns auto open doors on/off. When on, doors will automatically open when you approach them.
FortSetting.AutoPickupWeaponsConsolePC_Description: Turns auto pick up weapons on/off. When on, weapons will automatically be picked up when moving over them, unless your inventory is full.
FortSetting.AutoPickupWeapons_Description: Turns auto pick up weapons on/off. When on, weapons will automatically be picked up when moving over them, unless your inventory is full.
FortSetting.AutoSortConsumablesToHigherSlots_Descrip: Turns auto sort consumables to higher numbered slots on/off. When on, consumable items such as health and shields will default to the highest empty quickbar slot when picked up.
FortSetting.AutoSortConsumablesToRight_Description: Turns auto sort consumables to right on/off. When on, consumable items such as health and shields will default to the rightmost empty quickbar slot when picked up.
FortSetting.GamepadAutoRun_Description: Turns controller auto-run on/off. When on, double clicking the left stick will make you automatically run forward without needing to hold the stick forward.
FortSetting.EditModeAimAssist_Description: Turns edit mode aim assist on/off. When on, this attracts your controller aim to the closest editing square in building edit mode.
FortSetting.TouchEdit_Description: Turns edit selection with touch on/off.
FortSetting.BackgroundAudio_Description: Turns game audio on/off when the game is in the background. When on, the game audio will continue to play when the game is minimized, or another window is focused.
FortSetting.ShowGlobalChat_Description: Turns global chat on/off. When on, you will see and be able to send messages in global chat.
FortSetting.ReplayHighQualityRecording_Description: Turns high quality replay recording on/off. When on, causes replays to record data more frequently, and disables some other optimizations which can cause visual issues during playback. Recording high quality replays can reduce performance and take up hard drive space.
FortSetting.InvertPitch_Description: Turns look inversion on/off.  When on, your character will look down when the control is moved up.
FortSetting.CreativeTurboDelete_Description: Turns on/off the ability to rapidly delete things in creative mode by holding down the delete button.
FortSetting.PeripheralLighting_Description: Turns peripheral lighting on/off for supported devices.
FortSetting.ReplayRecordingCreativeMode_Description: Turns replay recording on/off for Creative Mode matches. Recording creative replays can reduce performance and take up hard drive space.
FortSetting.ReplayRecordingLargeTeams_Description: Turns replay recording on/off for large team modes. When on, replays are recorded and stored after each match with large teams, such as 50v50 or Teams of 20. Recording large team replays can reduce performance and take up hard drive space.
FortSetting.ReplayRecording_Description: Turns replay recording on/off. When on, replays are recorded and stored after each match. Recording replays can reduce performance and take up hard drive space.
FortSetting.EquipFirstBuildingPieceWhenSwappingQuick: Turns reset building choice on/off. When on, switching to build mode will always bring up the first build piece. When off, the game will remember and bring up the last build piece you were using.
Turns reset building choice on/off. When on, switching to build mode will always bring up the first build piece. When off, the game will remember and bring up the last build piece you were using.
FortSetting.ShowSpectatorCount_Description: Turns spectator count on/off. When on, a count of players spectating you is shown on the in-game HUD in the lower left.
FortSetting.TapToInteract_Description: Turns tap to search/interact on/off. When on, search/interact will require a single press. When off, the search/interact control must be held for the duration of the timer.
FortSetting.ReplayRecordingIndicator_Description: Turns the recording indicator on/off. When on, a red dot and REC text will pop up at the top right corner of the screen whenever your match is being recorded.
FortSetting.VisualizeAudioSources_Description: Turns the visual radial indicator for some sounds on/off.  When on, you will see the visual radial indicator for some sounds, but in game sound will no longer pan or provide spatialization. Creators may set this to OFF for their island experience, which will override your selection.
FortSetting.VisualizeAudioSourcesWithSpat_Descriptio: Turns the visual radial indicator for some sounds on/off.  When on, you will see the visual radial indicator for some sounds. Creators may set this to OFF for their island experience, which will override your selection.
FortSetting.TurboBuild_Description: Turns turbo building on/off. When on, holding down the build button will automatically continue to build the selected piece when looking around. Turning off will set each building to require one press or click.
FortSetting.TSR_Description:
Unreal Engine's Temporal Super Resolution displays similarily detailed images with reduced load on your GPU for each frame. When enabled, it allows you to prioritize performance or quality.

Recommended (default): Selects the 3D resolution based what works best for your display resolution.

Performance: Prioritise frame rate over final image quality by rendering at lower resolution.

Balanced: Balances the image quality versus performance.

Quality: Prioritise final image quality over performance by rendering at higher resolution.

Native: Allows you to render frames at the native display resolution at the expense of performance.

Custom: Allows you to customize the 3D resolution on a slider.
FortSetting.TriggerHapticsUseThreshold_Description: Use Adaptive Trigger effect to trigger button presses. Disabling this will use the default trigger thresholds to detect button presses.
FortSetting.EnableRudderControl_Description: Use a foot device as input if connected.
FortSetting.MoveStickAccelerates_Description: Using the move stick accelerates or brakes the vehicle you're driving. When disabled, the move stick is only for steering while all accelerating and braking is handled by the controller triggers. This option only affects vehicles where you can accelerate and brake with the triggers.
FortSetting.ColorBlindStrength_Description: Using the provided images, adjust the strength of the filter until you see the color correction that works best for you. There is a llama shape in the middle of each circle.
FortSetting.ColorBlindMode_Description: Using the provided images, test out the different color blind modes of the filter until you see the color correction that works best for you. There is a llama shape in the middle of each circle.
FortSetting.VSyncDisabledBecauseOfFrameGeneration: VSync must be disabled when NVIDIA DLSS Frame Generation is enabled.
FortSetting.TouchVerticalSensitivity_Description: Vertical Sensitivity Multiplier for Touch Input.
FortSetting.ViewDistance_Description: View distance determines how far away objects are culled for performance.
FortSetting.TimeReportsActionDescription: View how much time your child has spent in Fortnite and Unreal Editor for Fortnite (UEFN) each week.
FortSetting.ReticleColorForEnemy_Description: What color the reticle is when an enemy is in range
FortSetting.QuickWeaponToggleFunction_Description: What should happen when you tap Quick Weapon if your primary item is already selected? Toggling between slots 1 and 2 or your most recently equipped item can be helpful for quickly moving back and forth between your favorite two items.
FortSetting.GyroActiveBuildMode_Description:
When building or editing, when should gyro aiming be active?

If set to ALWAYS, it's a good idea to have another way to disable the gyro so you can reset your controller position. You can do this by setting Look Stick Effect to DISABLES (below) or customizing your controls to include a Gyro Modifier button in the Controller customization tab.
FortSetting.GyroActiveBuildMode_MobileDescription:
When building or editing, when should gyro aiming be active?

If set to ALWAYS, it's a good idea to have another way to disable the gyro so you can reset your device position. You can do this by setting Touch Effect to DISABLES (below).
FortSetting.ADSFire_Description: When enabled, pressing the touch look & fire button will also aim down sights / aim down scope. While Held means that releasing the touch look & fire button will also exit aiming down sights / scope.
FortSetting.DisablePreEditsWhenPlacingBuilding_Descr: When on, edit option will be disabled when placing the building piece.
FortSetting.STW_ConsoleUnlockedFPS_Description: When on, maximizes framerate but will lead to inconsistent performance and higher input lag.
FortSetting.FollowCamera_Description: When on, moving left or right also turns the camera at the same time as long as you're not aiming or firing. Enable this if using two sticks all the time is difficult for you. The right stick still functions as normal, so you can still learn to get comfortable with the right stick with this feature enabled.
FortSetting.TouchFollowCamera_Description: When on, moving left or right also turns the camera at the same time as long as you're not aiming or firing. This can make it easier to run around while keeping your right thumb free for other actions. You can still take control of the camera at any time by touching the right side of the screen.
FortSetting.PingPlaceDangerMarkerWhenTargeting_Descr: When placing a marker, if you are Targeting (ADS) when you ping, then a danger marker will be placed instead of the default location marker.
FortSetting.WindingSpeed_Description: When rotating the flick stick, how fast does it turn the camera?
FortSetting.GyroActiveMode_Description:
When should gyro aiming be active? Only when aiming your weapon? When harvesting materials? All the time?

If set to ALWAYS, it's a good idea to have another way to disable the gyro so you can reset your controller position. You can do this by setting Look Stick Effect to DISABLES (below) or customizing your controls to include a Gyro Modifier button in the Controller customization tab.
FortSetting.GyroActiveMode_MobileDescription:
When should gyro aiming be active? Only when aiming your weapon? When harvesting materials? All the time?

If set to ALWAYS, it's a good idea to have another way to disable the gyro so you can reset your device position. You can do this by setting Touch Effect to DISABLES (below).
FortSetting.EnableTryBuildOnFocus_Description: When switching to a different build piece, using Builder Pro, it will try to build immediately.
FortSetting.EasyLootGridEnabled_Warning: When the Easy Loot widget is visible, it will disable other modes of interaction.
FortSetting.ResolutionForcedNative: When the Window Mode is set to <strong>Windowed Fullscreen</>, the resolution must match the native desktop resolution.
FortSetting.CameraResetAxes_Description:
Which axes get reset by the Reset Camera button?

If PITCH or BOTH are selected, pressing the Reset Camera button will bring the camera back to looking at the horizon.

If YAW or BOTH are selected, pressing the Reset Camera button will flick the camera to face the direction the Move Stick is pointing. For example, quickly look behind you by moving backwards and pressing the Reset Camera button. If the Move Stick is not engaged, the Reset Camera button will have no effect on the camera's yaw.
FortSetting.QuickWeaponButtonGroup_Description: While Quick Weapon is held, which group of buttons should be used for selecting weapons? Use the directional pad, the face buttons, or both.
FortSetting.TextChat_Desc:
While in a party with friends or when teamed up with random players during a match, a text chat channel becomes available. This setting controls whether or not this account can receive or send messages in the text chat channel.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Note</>: This setting disables Fortnite's in-game text chat. The platform you are playing on may have additional communication features that must be restricted separately. For information on platform specific controls please use the "More Settings" button.
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: You can send and receive text chat messages with your teammates.
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: You cannot send or receive text chat messages with your teammates.
FortSetting.VoiceChat_ParentalControls_Description_E:
While in a party with friends or when teamed up with random players during a match, a voice chat channel becomes available. This setting controls who your child can voice chat with.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Everybody</>: Your child can voice chat with any player.
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Friends & Teammates</>: Your child can voice chat with players in their Epic friends list and platform friends list, and those on their team.
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Friends Only</>: Your child can voice chat only with players in their Epic friends list and platform friends list.
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Nobody</>: Epic voice chat is disabled for your child.
FortSetting.VoiceChat_VRR_ParentalControls_Descripti:
While in a party with friends or when teamed up with random players during a match, a voice chat channel becomes available. This setting controls who your child can voice chat with. Turning on voice chat also turns on voice reporting.

<strong>Everybody</> : Your child can voice chat with any player.

<strong>Friends & Teammates</> : Your child can voice chat with players in their Epic friends list and their platform friends list, and those on their team.

<strong>Friends Only</> : Your child can voice chat only with players in their Epic friends list and platform friends list.

<strong>Off</> : Voice chat and voice reporting is off.

<strong>About Voice Reporting</>

When voice chat is on, voice reporting stores voice chat audio on each participants device on a rolling five - minute basis, which will be sent to Epic Games only if a participant reports a violation. Voice reporting is usually on, except in parties formed among friends where all players prefer voice reporting off. Players can see if voice reporting is currently on or off in the Sidebar. Voice reporting is always on for players under 18.

See the voice reporting setting for more details and options.
FortSetting.ShowTextChat_Description:
While in the lobby a text chat window is available to send and receive messages from friends and other party members. This setting controls whether or not this account can receive or send messages in the text chat window from friends or other party members

NOTE: This setting disables Fortnites in-game text chat only. The platform you are playing on may have additional communication features that must be restricted separately.
FortSetting.VoiceChatRVR_Description:
While using Fortnite's voice chat with voice reporting on, each participant's device will capture and store voice chat audio on a rolling five - minute basis, which will be sent to Epic Games only if a participant reports a chat violation to help us evaluate the report.

You can see if voice reporting is currently on or off in the Sidebar.
